    "en": {
      "title": "A 9-year-old child died",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "According to the Sevanagala Police, a nine-year-old child drowned yesterday (05th) while swimming in Ate Canal in Mahagama Urusitawewa, which belongs to the Sevanagala Police Domain.",
        "The deceased was a child named Dasun Induwara Samaraweera, a resident of Pelagahawatta West in Hakmana Narawalpita.",
        "This child was studying in Gnanaloka Pirivene at the Mahagama Subhadrarama Temple and was aspiring for ordination.",
        "Twelve lay monks, including the temple vicar, had gone to the canal to swim with this boy.",
        "While swimming in the canal, the child drifted down the canal and drowned.",
        "The child was recovered and taken to the Sevanagala Regional Hospital, but the investigation revealed that the child had already died. The autopsy on the child's death is scheduled to be held today (06th) at Embilipitiya Base Hospital."
      ],
